def fixClose(series, ref, max_move = 20):
    abs_moves = (df[series].diff(periods=1)[1:]).abs()
    # for one anomaly we observe two consecutives abnormal moves. The anomaly is at the first date
    anom_dates = abs_moves[abs_moves>=max_move].index   
    
    df.loc[anom_dates[::2],series] = df.loc[anom_dates[::2],ref] * np.array(df.loc[anom_dates[1::2],series]/df.loc[anom_dates[1::2],ref])
    print(anom_dates[::2])

In order to make the series first order stationary we consider the log-return

In [37]:
def bivVol(start,end):
    return np.square(bivReturn(start, end,False))

def univVol(x):
    return np.square(bivReturn(x.shift(), x,False))
    

def bivReturn(start,end,loga = True):
    if loga:
        return bivMove(np.log(start), np.log(end))
    else:
        return bivMove(start, end)/start

def univReturn(x,loga = True):
    return bivReturn(x.shift(),x,loga)

def bivMove(start,end):
    return end - start
def univMove(x):
    return bivMove(x.shift(),x.shift())

# lags = [3,6]

# weights = [1,2,1]
def generateFeature(mdata,lags = [3,6],weights=None):
    if not weights:
        weights = np.ones(len(lags))
    snames = ['Signal.l%s'%lag for lag in lags if lag!=0]
    if 0 in lags:
        snames = 'Signal' + snames

    mdata['SignalFeature'] = np.array(mdata[snames]) @ np.array(weights)/ np.sum(weights)
    mdata['SignalFeatureLogReturn'] = univReturn(mdata['SignalFeature'])
    return mdata
data = generateFeature(data)
data_train = generateFeature(data_train)

In [61]:
date_str = lambda x: x.strftime('%m/%d/%Y')

def pnlSimple(mdata,amount,returnName,signalName,thld_buy=-100,thld_sell=-100,plot_dist = False,trading_cost=1):
    
    c = trading_cost/10000 #trading cost is in bps. c is the trading cost per 1 dollar of order.
    output = list()
    hold = False
    if thld_buy==-100 and thld_sell==-100:
        hold = True
    
    if hold:
        output.append('Long the ETF every day')
    else:
        output.append('Long the ETF when S>%d%%, Short when S<%d%%'%(100*thld_buy,100*thld_sell))
    sign = - 1*(mdata[signalName]<thld_sell) + 1*(mdata[signalName]>thld_buy) 
    
    if(plot_dist):
        title = 'Returns distribution from %s to %s'%(date_str(mdata.index[0]),date_str(mdata.index[-1]))
        fig = plt.figure(figsize=(8,8))
        sns.histplot(data=mdata[sign==1], x=yrname, color="skyblue", label="Positive signal", kde=True)
        if(hold):
            fig.legend(labels=['Buy days'])
        else:
            sns.histplot(data=mdata[sign==-1], x=yrname, color="red", label="Negative signal", kde=True)
            sns.histplot(data=mdata[sign==0], x=yrname, color="grey", label="Mixed signal", kde=True).set_title(title)
            fig.legend(labels=['Buy days','Sell days','Flat Days'])

    r_hold = np.exp(mdata[returnName])-1
    r = r_hold * sign
    if hold:
        r[0]-=c
        r[r[r != 0].index[-1]] -=c
    else:
        r[r!=0] -= 2*c 

    output.append('%d trading days from %s to %s' %(mdata.shape[0],date_str(mdata.index[0]),date_str(mdata.index[-1])))
    output += lreturnStats(r,amount)
    return output

We invest the same amount every day and clear the portfolio between each day

def lreturnStats(r,amount):
    r_traded = r[r!=0]
    pnl = amount*np.sum(r)
    output = list()
    output.append('Daily acount size: $%d'%amount)
    output.append('Total PnL: $%d'%pnl)
    
    aer = 100*(np.prod(r+1)**(252/len(r)) - 1)
    output.append('Annualized Return: %.2f%%'%aer)
    std = 100*(r_traded.std() * np.sqrt(252))
    output.append('Annual Standard Deviation: %.2f%%'%std)
    sr = r_traded.mean()/r_traded.std() * np.sqrt(252)
    output.append('Sharpe Ratio: %.2f'%sr)
    ppd = len(r_traded)/len(r)
    output.append('Proportion of days traded: %.2f'%ppd)
    ppm = np.mean(r_traded>0)
    output.append('Proportion of positive days: %.2f'%ppm)
    
    s=(r+1).cumprod()
    dd = np.ptp(s)/s.max()
    output.append('Maximum drawdown: %.2f'%dd)
    return output
